[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Transparency and accountability[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The FMB believes that greater transparency in relation to the proportion of SME firms that local authorities and other public sector clients procure from, would gradually increase SME engagement. It would boost the proportion of work being awarded to SME firms by providing the star performers with positive feedback and media attention (such as the newly introduced ‘best councils to do business with’ awards) and the worst performers with negative feedback. It is likely to create a sense of healthy competition among neighbouring local authorities and drive up performance across the board.
